title: Video: Aerial views of Atlas 5’s rollout with Lucy
summary: The 188-foot-tall Atlas 5 rocket crowned with NASA’s Lucy asteroid probe rolled out to its launch pad Thursday at Cape Canaveral. These aerial views, captured by a drone and released by NASA, show the launch vehicle moving along rail tracks to Space Launch Complex 41.

title: Starliner valve investigation continues to focus on moisture interaction with propellant
summary: Boeing’s CST-100 Starliner was within hours of launch on its second uncrewed test flight in early August when stuck valves in the spacecraft’s propulsion system forced a launch scrub that has turned into a delay that will extend well into next year.

title: Shenzhou-13 heads for space station after reaching orbit
summary: A second crew of three astronauts are heading for China’s Tianhe space station module after the successful launch of the Shenzhou-13 mission Friday.

title: My Favorite Martian Image: the Ridges of 'South Séítah'
summary: NASA’s Perseverance rover captures a geologic feature with details that offer clues to the area’s mysterious past.

title: Shenzhou 13 launches first long-duration Chinese Space Station crew
summary: After a successful launch to the new Chinese Space Station earlier this year and the initial 90-day “shakedown cruise” of the Shenzhou 12 crew, three taikonauts launched to the station aboard the Shenzhou 13 spacecraft to begin the first long-duration stay aboard.

title: China repeats call for international astronauts to join space station crews
summary: On the eve of the next crew launch to the Chinese space station, a spokesperson for China’s human spaceflight agency repeated Thursday the country’s invitation for international astronauts to fly to the new orbiting space lab.

title: BepiColombo's first tastes of Mercury science
summary: The magnetic and particle environment around Mercury was sampled by BepiColombo for the first time during the mission's close flyby of the planet at 199 km on 1-2 October 2021, while the huge gravitational pull of the planet was felt by its accelerometers.

title: Three astronauts begin half-year mission on Chinese space station
summary: Three astronauts floated into the living quarters of China’s space station Friday, hours after launching from a military-run spaceport in the Gobi Desert, moving in for a six-month mission to prepare the outpost for expansion next year.
